    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- What is MT4 Section -->
  <section class="section section--alt" id="what-is-mt4">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2 class="heading-2">What is MetaTrader 4?</h2>
          <p>
            MetaTrader 4 (MT4) is the world's most widely used retail forex trading platform. Developed by MetaQuotes Software and released in 2005, it has become the industry standard for forex and CFD trading with over 16 million traders worldwide.
          </p>
          <p>
            Simply put, MetaTrader 4 is a trading platform that provides retail traders leverage and access to a wide array of tools for trading. With these tools, you can build and develop a sophisticated trading algorithm, or simply use the platform for day-trading financial instruments offered by your broker.
          </p>
          <p>
            MT4 is popular because it combines powerful charting tools, technical analysis capabilities, and automated trading through Expert Advisors (EAs) in one user-friendly package. It's available for free through any MT4-supporting broker.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Important:</strong> MetaTrader 4 is not owned by a brokerage, nor is MT4 a broker. It's a third-party platform that brokers license to allow trading. Brokers pay MetaQuotes to use the software, which allows their systems to trade via the platform.
          </p>

          <h3>MetaTrader 4 Summary</h3>
          <p>
            Traders love MT4. It's been around since the very beginning of retail trading, and for that reason, it has a huge following. There are a large number of addons, customisations and Trading Robots, known on MT4 as "Expert Advisors" (EAs).
          </p>
          <p>
            There's the ability to add trading signals and more, all specifically built for MT4. These addons are cross-compatible with MT5, but MT5 doesn't offer a great deal different, so many traders have decided to stick with what they know, which has kept MT4 as the popular choice.
          </p>
          <p>
            Development and support will eventually end on MT4 and MetaQuotes will force brokers and users to make the switch to MT5, in most cases reluctantly. However, for now, MT4 remains the dominant platform.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="quick-facts">
            <h3>MT4 Quick Facts</h3>
            <dl>
              <dt>Released</dt>
              <dd>2005</dd>
              <dt>Developer</dt>
              <dd>MetaQuotes Software</dd>
              <dt>Cost</dt>
              <dd>Free</dd>
              <dt>Best For</dt>
              <dd>Forex, EAs, CFDs</dd>
              <dt>Platforms</dt>
              <dd>Win, Mac, Web, Mobile</dd>
              <dt>Users</dt>
              <dd>16+ Million</dd>
            </dl>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-box">
            <h4>Start Trading on MT4</h4>
            <p><strong>AvaTrade</strong> offers MT4 with:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Multi-regulation (FCA, ASIC)</li>
              <li>0.9 pip spreads</li>
              <li>Full EA support</li>
              <li>Welcome bonus available</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/brokers/avatrade/partner-code/" class="btn btn-primary btn-full">Get AvaTrade Partner Code</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pros and Cons -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="heading-2 text-center">Should You Use MetaTrader 4?</h2>
      <p class="section-intro text-center">Based on 28+ hours of research, expert reviews, and hands-on testing, here's what traders think:</p>

      <div class="pros-cons-grid">
        <div class="pros-card">
          <h3>‚úÖ 7 Reasons To Use MetaTrader 4</h3>
          <ul>
            {reasonsToUse.map((reason) => (
              <li>{reason}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons-card">
          <h3>‚õî 1 Reason Not To Use MetaTrader 4</h3>
          <ul>
            {reasonsNotToUse.map((reason) => (
              <li>{reason}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

